Music for Life will be an Australian based foundation that helps young people with musical talent record their music in a professional environment without the stress of affordability as most of the production cost is waivered with support from local and international sponsors with a series of concerts held each year to raise funds to help young people get the push to get themselves out there..
Each year most of the talent in the music industry is missed because, for some it is just not an affordable option to record their music. One out of ten of the musicians in this situation are probably the next big name you hear on the radio , but getting from here to there is so hard when the only person hearing them is close friends and relatives in-between the walls of their house . Our main focus is getting the unknown musicians out there at no cost and providing them with support through various social networking channels to turn their life around and give them a positive break into a hard industry.
Just like the old days when “Elvis” walked in off the street and became “the king” we want to be able to change people’s lives forever through the power of music.
With help and donations from local and international sponsors together in one cause , we can make this foundation a reality , all we need to get moving along is the basic equipment and knowledge to go together to help form something for everyone that counts in a big way.
When everything is finalized we hope to help a broad range of people, by donating most of the proceeds of every popular recording to selected charities other than ours.
If you have anything that might be of help to us such as a studio “a mixing desk, an old guitar or two, or even knowledge how to use some modern recording equipment, we could use your help as with your support we can achieve something great that every unearthed musician needs “a chance”.

lender.occupational_info:
What is Powwow-aeaa Earth Kids project
SPIRIT / NATURE / TECHNOLOGY Earth is one big family, made up of 6.8 billion human beings and 30 million kinds of living species. What can we do to save the beautiful earth for our kids in the future? Spirit, Nature and Technology, the three in harmony is what we need as we dive into the mid-21st century. To obtain this balance, we need to go beyond the differences in religion, race and ideaology, and get out of the materialistic way of living. Each of us needs to start relating directly to the world in our own way and remember to dream. Powwow is a Native American ceremony of dance and music. aeaa stands for Asia, Europe, Africa, and America. It is an important message that kids from around the world hand in hand, start to act together to save the earth for children yet to be born. The seven nature Usagi reck, hiki, ras, yang, divan, song, and haman are fighting for our earth, to shift our way of living to a more sustainable way. Powwow-aeaa Earth Kids Project is an art movement, children and grown-ups - by thinking and expressing ideas about the earth - get connected to the earth through art, creating a movement.

lender.name: Roy
lender.occupational_info:
About America’s Business Leaders:
America's Business Leaders is a human development company that was founded in 2005 by Roy Juarez, Jr, then a freshman at Hardin-Simmons University. Roy has always had a passion for working with the community. At the age of 12 he created and headed a community youth outreach program in San Antonio, TX. However, at the age of 14 Roy became homeless with a 9 year old sister and 2 year old brother, due to a violent divorce. After spending two and a half years as a “couch surfer” living in dozens of homes, he found a stable family that would take him in. Today, Roy speaks to audiences across the country and abroad, entering some of America's toughest neighborhoods with the hope that sharing his story will inspire and provide hope. He recently appeared on CNN with his mentor Lieutenant Colonel Consuelo Castillo Kickbusch, US Army (RET) in a segment leading up to Latinos in America. His spell-binding story has caught the attention of the well-established New York Times bestseller Chicken Soup for the Soul series. In August of 2009 Roy’s Story was featured in their latest book Chicken Soup for the Soul: Extraordinary Teens.
